# DateInterval

You can calculate the difference between two dates using `diff()`, which returns a `DateInterval` object.

```php
$start = new DateTime('2025-01-01');
$end   = new DateTime('2025-12-31');
$interval = $start->diff($end);
echo $interval->days; // 364 (or 365? depends on leap year)
echo $interval->format('%R%a days'); // +364 days
```

